					Full Description



Tronox Limited, incorporated on September 21, 2011, is engaged in the production and marketing of titanium bearing mineral sands and titanium dioxide (TiO2) pigment. The Company also produces natural soda ash. The Company operates through two segments: TiO2 and Alkali. Its TiO2 segment includes exploration, mining, and beneficiation of mineral sands deposits; production of titanium feedstock, including chloride slag, slag fines, synthetic rutile and leucoxene, pig iron and zircon; production and marketing of TiO2, and electrolytic manganese dioxide manufacturing and marketing, which is primarily focused on battery materials and specialty boron products. Its Alkali segment includes dry mining of trona ore underground at its Westvaco facility; secondary recovery of trona from previously dry mined areas underground at its Westvaco and Granger facilities through solution mining; refining of raw trona ore into soda ash and specialty sodium alkali products, and marketing, sale and distribution of alkali products.The Company's TiO2 is used in a range of products in the manufacturing of paint and other coatings, plastics and paper, and in a range of other applications, including inks, fibers, rubber, food, cosmetics and pharmaceuticals. The Company's soda ash products are used by customers in the glass, detergent and chemicals manufacturing industries. The Company has operations in North America, Europe, South Africa and the Asia-Pacific region. Within its TiO2 segment, the Company operates three pigment production facilities at locations, such as Hamilton, Mississippi; Botlek, the Netherlands, and Kwinana, Western Australia. It also operates three separate mining operations: KwaZulu-Natal (KZN) Sands and Namakwa Sands both located in South Africa, and Cooljarloo located in Western Australia.The Company's KwaZulu-Natal Sands operations located in South Africa consists of the Fairbreeze mine, a concentration plant, a mineral separation plant and a smelter complex. The Company's Namakwa Sands operations located in South Africa include the Namakwa Sands mine, a primary concentration plant, a secondary concentration plant, a mineral separation plant and a smelter complex. Its Western Australia operations consists of the Cooljarloo Sands mine and concentration plant, and the Chandala processing plant, which includes a mineral separation plant and a synthetic rutile plant. As of December 31, 2016, the Company's TiO2 operations had a combined annual production capacity of approximately 750,000 metric tons (MT) of titanium feedstock, which consisted of 91,000 MT of rutile and leucoxene, 220,000 MT of synthetic rutile, and 410,000 MT of titanium slag. As of December 31, 2016, its TiO2 operations produced approximately 220,000 MT of zircon and 221,000 MT of pig iron. As of December 31, 2016, it supplied and marketed TiO2 under the brand name TRONOX to approximately 1,200 customers in over 100 countries.The Company provides its soda ash to a range of industries, such as flat glass, container glass, detergent and chemical manufacturing. The Company produces natural soda ash from a mineral called trona, which it mines at two sites in the Green River Basin, Wyoming. The Company's Wyoming facilities process the trona ore into chemically pure soda ash and specialty sodium products, such as sodium bicarbonate (baking soda). The Company sells soda ash directly to customers in the United States, Canada and Europe and to the American Natural Soda Ash Corporation (ANSAC). It uses a portion of its soda ash at Green River to produce specialty sodium products, such as sodium bicarbonate and sodium sesquicarbonate that has uses in food, animal feed pharmaceutical and medical applications. As of December 31, 2016, its Alkali segment produced approximately four million tons of soda ash and downstream specialty products. Trona is dry mined underground at its Westvaco facility primarily through the operation of its longwall mining machine. The Company solution mines trona at both its Westvaco and Granger sites using secondary recovery techniques. The Sesqui and Mono plants, located at its Westvaco site, convert dry-mined trona into soda ash. The Company sells refined sodium sesquicarbonate under the names S-Carb and Sesqui. The Company sells its alkali-products to customers directly in the United States, Canada, the European Community, the European Free Trade Area and the South African Customs Union.The Company competes with Solvay Chemicals, Ciner Resources, L.P., Tata Chemicals Soda Ash Partners, Searles Valley Minerals, Church & Dwight Co., Natural Soda LLC, Chemours, Cristal Global, Huntsman, Kronos Worldwide Inc., Lomon Billions, CNNC and Blue Star.

» Full Overview of TROX.N







