A BRIGHTER FUTURE - FROM THE GROUND UP
 Our primary trona bed is located 1,600 feet underground and averages...
Read More 

About Tronox Alkali
Tronox Alkali operates a multi-faceted mining and production facility in Green River, Wyoming, supplying some of the best-known products used around the globe. We are the world’s largest producer of natural soda ash and strive to harness the latest technological innovations to better serve our customers.
Tronox Alkali employs approximately 950 people at eight processing plants and an underground mining operation that is 1,600 feet (488 meters) below the Earth’s surface. We are proud of employing several generations of reliable, hard-working families over many decades and are determined to maintain a culture of safety as a core value.
About Tronox Alkali – Trifold Brochure
Tronox Alkali Product Literature
50 Million Years of History
The Green River story began some 50 million years ago, when this Wyoming site was at the bottom of a 1,000 square-mile body of water called Lake Gosiute. Over millions of years, runoff from the surrounding mountains carried sodium-rich compounds into the lake. That sodium reacted with carbon dioxide to form the mineral called trona. In time, this reaction created the largest trona deposit in the world, and, as Lake Gosiute dried up, an estimated 130 billion short tons (1.18 billion metric tons) of trona were deposited across the Green River Basin.
Trona ore is naturally occurring sodium sesquicarbonate.  Since discovery of the trona beds in 1938, the Green River Basin has become the preferred source of high quality soda ash and other sodium products that ship worldwide.
Vital to Everyday Products
From trona ore we make soda ash, sodium bicarbonate, S-Carb®, Sesqui™ and sodium hydroxide.  Soda ash is an essential component in making glass, fiberglass, detergents, tableware, lighting, and display screens for consumer electronics.  Sodium bicarbonate, commonly known as baking soda, has countless applications including those in foods, an array of consumer products, and pharmaceuticals.  S-Carb® is the preferred ingredient in animal feed to balance rumen pH and provide electrolytes for poultry and swine.  Sesqui™ sodium sesquicarbonate provides the silky clean feeling in bath salts and many cleaning compounds.
The Green River operation has been mining trona for roughly seven decades and today produces more than 4 million short tons (3.63 million metric tons) annually. Tronox Alkali ships approximately 40,000 railcars and 5,000 truck orders of trona each year. And we do it all more efficiently and economically, on a delivered basis, than synthetic competitors anywhere in the world. Tronox Alkali has its corporate offices in Philadelphia.

 























